<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910318-0030</DOCNO><DOCID>910318-0030.</DOCID><HL>   Marketing Brief -- General Electric Co.:   NBC, Broadcast Operations   Report a 21% Profit Decline</HL><DATE>03/18/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6</SO><CO>   GE</CO><IN>MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   General Electric Co.'s National Broadcasting Co. and otherbroadcasting businesses posted a 21% decline in operatingprofit for 1990 as revenue fell 5%, the parent company saidin its latest annual report.   The NBC network, seven company-owned NBC stations, andNBC's cable interests combined posted pretax operating profitof $477 million last year, down sharply from $603 million in1989. Revenue fell to $3.24 billion from $3.39 billion, theannual report said.</LP><TEXT>   GE doesn't usually break out broadcasting results on aquarterly basis, giving details of results only at year end.The NBC network posted declines in revenue and profit asratings fell and ad spending slowed, the report said. NBCofficials declined to comment on the results.</TEXT></DOC>